value.title: The Trump administration is considering shortening the recommended quarantine time for Covid-19
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump's coronavirus task force is reviewing evidence about how long people need to quarantine to be safe and slow the spread of Covid-19, according to Assistant Secretary for Health Adm. Brett Giroir.

value.title: Corn vs. Cob: Trump pardons 'lucky' Thanksgiving turkey but avoids political jokes
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump partook in an annual holiday tradition – the pardoning of the National Thanksgiving Turkey, a turkey named Corn.

value.title: Chalian on Biden's agenda: 'America First' is gone
value.excerpt: CNN's David Chalian explains how President-elect Joe Biden's approach to selecting his cabinet differs from President Trump's.

value.title: Biden emphasizes foreign policy team will 'lead the world, not retreat'
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden says that his newly named foreign policy and national security team will keep the nation "safe and secure" and will show that "America is back."

value.title: Josh Hawley criticizes Biden Cabinet picks as 'corporatists,' 'war enthusiasts' and Big Tech 'sellouts'
value.excerpt: Sen. Josh Hawley on Tuesday criticized President-elect Joe Biden's cabinet picks.

value.title: CDC ready for Biden transition: "This is what we've been waiting for"
value.excerpt: Leadership at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, beset by a Trump White House that was harshly critical of the agency's coronavirus response, are anticipating the Biden transition team and the change a new administration will bring, senior health officials tell CNN.

value.title: DC Comics 'investigating' Proud Boys for using its logo to advertise a pro-Trump march in Washington
value.excerpt: The company behind Superman is considering legal action after the Proud Boys used the DC Comics logo, according to an email obtained by Insider.

value.title: Pennsylvania certifies election results for Biden despite Trump legal challenges
value.excerpt: The Pennsylvania State Department certified the results of the presidential election in favor of President-elect Joe Biden and Vice President-elect Kamala Harris, Gov. Tom Wolf said Tuesday.

value.title: Joe Concha: Media coverage of Biden transition has been just like the campaign, 'no scrutiny'
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden’s transition period will be fawned over by the media compared with President Trump, Fox News contributor Joe Concha said on Tuesday.

value.title: An anonymous senior Trump campaign advisor said Trump 'basically just conceded' by 'recommending' that the GSA start the Biden-Harris transition
value.excerpt: Emily Murphy, the head of the General Services Administration, has allowed President-elect Joe Biden to access resources to begin the transition.

value.title: Can Manny Diaz resurrect Democrats? — Poll: Majority of GOP would support Trump in 2024 — Florida tops 18,000 Covid-19 deaths
value.excerpt: Is this the answer that Florida Democrats have been hoping for? Jumping into the fray — Former Miami Mayor Manny Diaz, who earned a reputation as a turnaround artist in his home city, is campaigning for an even tougher job: leading the floundering Florida Democratic Party.

value.title: Virginia Democrats, Thrilled With Biden Victory, Aren’t Looking for Carbon Copy
value.excerpt: Suburban women who played a huge role in Joe Biden’s victory are not convinced that they need a white man to win their governor’s race next year.

value.title: Even Trump's fiercest critics say he may have gotten some world affairs right
value.excerpt: Some experts, ex-diplomats and even President Donald Trump's opponents concede his overseas initiatives have produced limited, qualified successes.

value.title: Melania Trump receives 2020 White House Christmas tree
value.excerpt: The first lady stepped out on the North Portico of the White House to accept the tree, a 18.5-foot-high Fraser Fir from West Virginia.

value.title: GM flips to California’s side in pollution fight against Trump
value.excerpt: General Motors says it will no longer support the Trump administration's legal efforts to end California’s right to set its own clean-air standards

value.title: Trump is reportedly worried that his legal team is made up of 'fools that are making him look bad'
value.excerpt: The president did not like seeing Rudy Giuliani's hair dye dripping down the side of the attorney's face at a news conference.

value.title: Rep. Michael Waltz: Biden Cabinet picks represent 'headlong push' back to Obama-era foreign policy
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden's Cabinet choices indicate he will reprise the Obama administration's "disastrous" foreign policy, especially in the Middle East, Rep. Michael Waltz, R-Fla., warned on Monday.

value.title: Biden spotlights ‘enduring commitment’ to NATO in talk with alliance leader
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden on spoke on Monday with the head of North Atlantic Treaty Organization - better known as NATO – the more than 7 decade old security organization that bonds the U.S with much of Europe.

value.title: Biden picks Alejandro Mayorkas, a son of Jewish Cuban refugees, to lead the Department of Homeland Security
value.excerpt: Mayorkas was second-in-command at DHS under President Barack Obama. He would be the first immigrant and first Hispanic American to lead the department.

value.title: Biden to tap former Fed Chair Janet Yellen as Treasury secretary: report
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden will reportedly nominate former Federal Reserve Chair Janet Yellen to serve as Treasury secretary in his administration, which would make her the first female to hold the Cabinet post.

value.title: Keilar calls Sydney Powell a Trump 'scapegoat'
value.excerpt: CNN's Brianna Keilar takes a look at Trump's legal team distancing itself from Sydney Powell, a lawyer who spoke at the campaign's press conference laying out its case for widespread voter fraud.

value.title: GM Stops Backing Trump Administration in Emissions Fight With California
value.excerpt: General Motors will no longer back the administration in its legal battle to strip California’s authority to set its own fuel-efficiency regulations, saying GM’s goals for green cars are aligned with the state and the new Biden administration.

value.title: Befriended by Trump, Populists in Europe’s East Brace for Change
value.excerpt: Populist and authoritarian politicians in Central Europe, who viewed President Trump as a valuable ally, are bracing for the incoming Biden administration’s new stress on promoting democracy and the rule of law.

value.title: Melania Trump celebrates arrival of annual White House Christmas tree
value.excerpt: First lady Melania Trump on Monday celebrated the arrival of the annual White House Christmas tree — without President Trump or their son Barron Trump, who have attended the event in past

value.title: Biden picks Blinken, Mayorkas, Sullivan for key Cabinet positions
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden on Monday announced a number of key Cabinet appointments, including Antony Blinken as secretary of state, Alejandro Mayorkas as secretary of homeland security, and Avril Haines to serve as the first woman to lead the intelligence community, among other positions.
